This paper is primarily focused on network slicing, which is a key mechanism in the field of computer networking. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the use of SDN/NFV architecture, which falls under the category of cs.SD (Software Engineering). Additionally, the paper addresses issues related to infrastructure and admission control, which are relevant to the categories of cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the paper discusses security concerns related to network slicing, which falls under the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
